    "AbLSTM retrained corresponds to the AbLSTM model retrained on the same training set of AbNatiV (Methods).",
    "The first six columns report the area under the PR curve (shown in Fig. 2 and Supplementary Fig.",
    "8), assessing the ability of the models to separate sequences in the human test (T) or the human diverse >5% (D) sets from those from mouse, rhesus and PSSM-generated (column headers).",
    "The human diverse >5% dataset is used here as a control to specifically assess the ability of the AbNatiV to generalize to sequences distant from those in its training set.",
    "The last two columns quantify the ability of each model to reconstruct human sequences in each dataset (column header)."
